in his 100th anniversary year.

00:02:00.610 --> 00:02:02.970
So let me tell you a little
bit more about our guests.

00:02:02.970 --> 00:02:05.950
Jamie Bernstein is a narrator,
writer, and broadcaster

00:02:05.950 --> 00:02:09.639
who has transformed a
lifelong love of music

00:02:09.639 --> 00:02:11.680
into a career of
sharing her knowledge

00:02:11.680 --> 00:02:13.510
and excitement with others.

00:02:13.510 --> 00:02:16.240
She grew up in an atmosphere
bursting with music, theater,

00:02:16.240 --> 00:02:16.900
and literature.

00:02:16.900 --> 00:02:20.200
Her father, composer-conductor
Leonard Bernstein,

00:02:20.200 --> 00:02:23.080
together with her mother, the
pianist and actress Felicia

00:02:23.080 --> 00:02:30.610
Montealegre, created a
spontaneous, ebullient

00:02:30.610 --> 00:02:34.330
household that turned Jamie into
a lifelong cultural enthusiast.

00:02:34.330 --> 00:02:36.490
Inspired by her father's
lifelong impulse

00:02:36.490 --> 00:02:38.230
to share and teach,
Jamie has devised

00:02:38.230 --> 00:02:40.930
several ways of communicating
her own excitement

00:02:40.930 --> 00:02:42.760
about classical music.

00:02:42.760 --> 00:02:44.410
In addition to the
Bernstein Beat,

00:02:44.410 --> 00:02:47.230
a family concert about her
father modeled after his own

00:02:47.230 --> 00:02:50.200
groundbreaking Young
People's Concerts,

00:02:50.200 --> 00:02:53.020
Jamie has also written and
narrated concerts about Mozart

00:02:53.020 --> 00:02:56.380
and Aaron Copland, among
others, produced radio programs

00:02:56.380 --> 00:02:59.380
and documentaries on a
range of musical topics.

00:02:59.380 --> 00:03:02.170
And she's currently
at work on a memoir.

00:03:02.170 --> 00:03:05.620
Clive Gillinson became the
executive and artistic director

00:03:05.620 --> 00:03:08.950
of Carnegie Hall
in July of 2005.

00:03:08.950 --> 00:03:11.710
He manages all aspects of
the world-renowned venue,

00:03:11.710 --> 00:03:13.840
overseeing the teams
responsible for developing

00:03:13.840 --> 00:03:18.400
the artistic concepts for
Carnegie Hall presentations

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:21.520
in its three halls, from
orchestral concerts to chamber

00:03:21.520 --> 00:03:25.570
music, solo recitals to
jazz and popular music,

00:03:25.570 --> 00:03:28.570
and wide-ranging music education
and social impact programs that

00:03:28.570 --> 00:03:31.690
reach more than half a million
people annually in New York

00:03:31.690 --> 00:03:34.270
City and around the world.

00:03:34.270 --> 00:03:36.010
Clive considers
Leonard Bernstein

00:03:36.010 --> 00:03:38.980
to be one of the greatest
influences on his musical life.

00:03:38.980 --> 00:03:41.260
They worked together when
Clive was managing director

00:03:41.260 --> 00:03:43.090
of the London
Symphony Orchestra,

00:03:43.090 --> 00:03:45.286
collaborating on a number
of projects, including

00:03:45.286 --> 00:03:46.660
the founding of
the Pacific Music

00:03:46.660 --> 00:03:49.270
Festival in Sapporo, Japan.

